events.body:
~~I attempted to bring this branch up-to-date with Master to attempt to get the Travis CI build to pass, and followed the instructions for rebasing in `CONTRIBUTING.md` to squash my two commits down to one, but something went wrong and now many other files are affected that I never touched. I will  try to get everything going properly but if any maintainer wants to step in and fix it, please feel free. Only the additional few lines in `doc/release-notes.md` are my changes.~~

Everything is rebased properly, I think. Not sure why the Travis CI build is still failing.
@satwo Travis is failing because of the trailing whitespace at the end of the lines you've added. You'll need to remove it.
@fanquake Thank you! Had a feeling it was something like that, but wasn't sure how to read the lint error.
